--------------------------------------------------
NESTED DIRECTORY CREATION
--------------------------------------------------

    Command:

        mkdir -p a/b/c/d/e

    Meaning:

        • Creates multiple directories at once
        • No error if parent directories don’t exist

    Example:

        mkdir -p project/src/main/java

    Use case:
        Create project structure in one command


--------------------------------------------------
COPY WITH PERMISSIONS
--------------------------------------------------

    Command:

        cp -rp src_path dest_path

    Options:

        -r → Recursive (copy directories)
        -p → Preserve permissions, ownership, timestamps

    Example:

        cp -rp /var/www /backup/

    Use case:
        Backup files with original permissions intact


--------------------------------------------------
ABSOLUTE PATH
--------------------------------------------------

    Definition:

        Full path starting from root (/)

    Example:

        /home/ec2-user/app/file.txt

    Key Point:

        • Always starts with /
        • Works from anywhere


--------------------------------------------------
RELATIVE PATH
--------------------------------------------------

    Definition:

        Path relative to current directory

    Example:

        ./file.txt
        ../folder/file.txt

    Symbols:

        .   → Current directory
        ..  → Parent directory

    Use case:
        Short paths inside current working directory


--------------------------------------------------
MOVE / RENAME FILES
--------------------------------------------------

    Command:

        mv src_path dest_path

    Example (move file):

        mv file.txt /home/ec2-user/

    Example (rename file):

        mv oldname.txt newname.txt

    Example (move + rename):

        mv file.txt /home/ec2-user/newfile.txt


